SIMPLE: unwind
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unwind
<hw>Un*wind"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>unwindan</ets>. See 1st <er>Un-</er>, and <er>Wind</er> to
coil.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To wind off; to loose or separate, as what or
convolved; to untwist; to untwine; <as>as, to <ex>unwind</ex> thread; to
<ex>unwind</ex> a ball of yarn</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To disentangle.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unwind</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unwind
<hw>Un*wind"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be or become unwound; to be
capable of being unwound or untwisted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unwisdom</ent>⟦br⟧
